So earlier this morning as i was driving to go support my college friend on the occasion of his traditional marriage, i began to reflect on a few things. 
Top on the list is the caption in my last slide, swipe!
Isn’t it ironic how as humans, we always tend to only see the RESULTS/REWARDS others may have/show..forgetting that behind each result/reward you see, lies an unimaginable amount of work/sacrifice which often times you the observer may not be capable or willing to do. 
If only you would stop complaining and begin to count your blessings and work on what needs to be worked on, you would realize that sooner/later YOUR dreams would become a reality! It is possible! 
My dear friend, it’s time to get up and begin to water your grass and watch it go green(er) 🤗❤️
#MindYourOwn
#reflections
#HaroldAmenyahspeaks

My visit to Canada was nothing short of amazing thanks to my wonderful host  who made sure was i was well taken care of. Whew! Host of hosts. 🥺🤩

The highlight of my trip was my visit to Niagara Falls which I have documented in my latest #YouTube video. 

The Niagara falls mark the border between New York state and Ontario, Canada. The majority of Niagara Falls is comprised of the American Falls, which is located on the American side of the border, and the Canadian or “Horseshoe” Falls on the Canadian side.

I have grown to love water 💦 which means visits to beaches, waterfronts, resorts and waterfalls get me. 
That being said, i’m sure you can guess my excitement getting to visit #NiagaraFalls and crossing it out my #bucketList. 🗒️ 
Guys, the Falls is everything you have heard and imagine. Check out my experience at the falls on our #youtube channel (link in bio) and thank me later 🤗 😁 ❤️

Who here has ever thought of getting a hair transplant ? Gather here for a meeting!🌚
They say a man’s crown is their hair so ain’t nothing wrong if you want to keep that “crown” intact… right? 
My hairline started receding very early (uni days i think) due to excess testosterone levels and genetics and i won’t lie…i hated it. 😤😩
Back then there was no access to information and technology as much as there is now. 
As time went on, i resorted to some “manageable” ways of improving my hairline; got introduced to hair fibers which is a very good way of managing a receding hairline for a day (i mean it works just like make-up) and can be exhausting but i have been on it for several years (Toppik chop my money taya😭) 
Years down the line, I learnt about hair transplants and how it is helping people break that generational hairline curse (or something like that🥺) … seriously! Back then i couldn’t afford it. I started researching on it and then found out it works so went on to add it to my BUCKET list. 
Ladies and gentlemen, here i am today to finally fix my over 10 year hairline issue thanks to @realofhair (the best transplant center in Turkey) 
For those who are curious about how this goes, don’t worry the full video will be on my YouTube channel soon! 👍🏾🙏
